Sudan is expected to have received 3.4 million doses of the Covid-19 vaccine by the end of March. 

Reporting by Patrick Ilunga, Mohammed Momoh, Mawahib Abdallatif and Kemo Cham The East African country received 103,000 doses of the vaccine at in Kigali through the UN-led Covax initiative. A consignment of some 1,020,000 cAstraZeneca jabs arrived in the country on Tuesday night. Medics say the only proven means of controlling spread of the virus is wearing masks and screening of patients. Second psychiatric report to be produced on March 12 before court gives directions in the Sh14 million corruption case. The cumulative recoveries in the country now stand at 87,099.